<item>
            <title>[SPARK-26007] DataFrameReader.csv() should respect to spark.sql.columnNameOfCorruptRecord</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-26007</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The csv() method of DataFrameReader doesn&apos;t take into account the SQL config spark.sql.columnNameOfCorruptRecord while creating an instance of CSVOptions:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/blob/2d085c13b7f715dbff23dd1f81af45ff903d1a79/sql/core/src/main/scala/org/apache/spark/sql/DataFrameReader.scala#L491-L494&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/blob/2d085c13b7f715dbff23dd1f81af45ff903d1a79/sql/core/src/main/scala/org/apache/spark/sql/DataFrameReader.scala#L491-L494&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This should be fixed by passing sparkSession.sessionState.conf.columnNameOfCorruptRecord as a constructor parameter to CSVOptions. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
